## Rewriting History

To change a method from the parent, simply rewrite the EXACT same method in the child class, and put `@override` right above it.

```dart
class Animal {
  void speek() { print('...'); }
}

class Dog extends Animal {
  @override
  void speek() {
    print('Woof!'); // This replaces the parent's speek!
  }
}
```
The `@override` physically tells Dart: "Ignore the parent's version, use mine instead!"

## Getting the Best of Both Worlds

What if you want to use the parent's original method AND add your own flavor to it?

You can trigger the parent's old code from inside the new overridden code using `super`!

```dart
class CustomButton extends Button {
  @override
  void tap() {
    print('Playing cool sound effect!');
    super.tap(); // Now trigger the original parent tap logic!
  }
}
```

